<br>
When I was playing in Blackburrow awhile back I thought I might have found someone who was actually roleplaying. What was I thinking?? /bonk.  This person shouts something about his sister causing him to get killed, I don't remember exactly but the way it was said it sounded like it could be roleplaying. I made the mistake of responding with something incharacter with /shout. After that this person then replies in shout and is clearly not incharacter. I though his/her sister was in the game, nope. This person in shout starts talking about how she got on his computer and blah blah blah. I quit listening and just ignored the person.<br>
<br>
I would alot happier if people would just make this distinction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=katrennaoffv>Katrenna of FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/10/03 10:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=224.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: *beats*head*against*desk*</span><hr size=1> OOC<br>
